<?xml-model ../out/tls1.rnc application/relax-ng-compact-syntax?><div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:mods="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3" xmlns:tls="http://tls.kanripo.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" type="concept" xml:id="uuid-f192250b-eaa6-44d1-b59b-fc954df38692"><head>TURBAN</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">頭巾</item><item xml:lang="och">巾</item></list><div type="definition"><p>HAT in the form of a CLOTH TIED AROUND the HEAD.</p></div><div type="notes"><div type="old-chinese-criteria"><p>1. The general word for a turban is jīn 巾, and this type of headgear is worn as the only headgear.</p><p>2. Zé 幘 is rare in pre-Han times and refers to a piece of thin silk with which to stabilise the hair-bun which parts of which might hang down over the shoulders and down to the eyebrows. Above the zé 幘 one might, occasionally, wear a guān 冠 "hat".</p></div><div type="modern-chinese-criteria"><p>頭巾</p><p>網巾</p><p>抹額</p><p>抹頭</p><p>幘</p><p>巾幘</p><p>襆頭</p><p>綸巾</p><p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div><div type="pointers"/><div type="source-references"><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-67c97ad0-3944-4d76-b7c8-25be0e1ed222">HUANG JINGUI 1995</ref><title>古代文化詞異集類辨考 Gudai wenhua ci yi ji lei bian kao</title><biblScope unit="page">704</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-9eb4d944-6640-47a4-8398-cfe72a1c902f">SUN JI</ref><title>漢代無知文化資料圖說</title><biblScope unit="page">231</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl></listBibl></div><div type="words"><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-1a89185c-5552-479a-a046-ad8f7e9bcc0d"><form corresp="#uuid-7c786196-3d04-4420-a4b0-d3e35304284f"><orth>巾</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">jīn</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">krɯn</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">kin</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-ed26c035-76e0-40b1-b1f5-36c659344864"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">5</usg></gramGrp><def>headband, tied round the forehead</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-4ea94e94-1715-47bd-94d2-906e300b0d20"><form corresp="#uuid-4b5e66b2-210b-4ffe-9094-00b3cb3b11e3"><orth>帕</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">mò</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">mbraad</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">mɣat</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-4197bf0c-71ab-4068-80c2-5bc1d2f4ebb3"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">0</usg></gramGrp><def>headgear in the form of a headband indicating one's rank, often worn by the military, and by commoners</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-ee409eab-7aba-4a17-a9a1-f3af9293cf65"><form corresp="#uuid-347eb2e4-0ba1-4375-b894-0ed4098cdc29"><orth>幘</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">zé</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">skreeɡ</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">ʈʂɣɛk</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-939e2d55-59f8-4a53-b8db-8e0d6138c754"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-8717712d-14a4-4ae2-be7a-6e18e61d929b">n</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">3</usg></gramGrp><def>HAN: silken headband tied round the hair only, and not the forehead</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-4cbc7176-56bd-44bf-b7c7-543e686f3630"><form corresp="#uuid-610582c0-a1f7-4633-8fa0-b380185c0e61 #uuid-2567a27c-7643-4cf8-9da5-5ac6fe236ab5"><orth>帩頭</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">qiào tóu</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">smʰewɡs doo</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">tshiɛu du</pron></form><sense xml:id="uuid-17605c9c-80e5-4614-aeb5-f1d8c8365f72"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-a8e89bab-49e1-4426-b230-0ec7887fd8b4">NP</tls:syn-func><usg type="warring-states-currency">2</usg></gramGrp><def>headscarf</def></sense></entry></div></div>